        <img src="../images/solar/Chondrite%20Meteorite.jpg" alt="Chondrite Meteorite" border="1" width="170" height="197" class="left">
    <b>Chondrite Meteorite</b>
    <br>
    This meteorite fell in 1970 in Cherokee County, Oklahoma.
    It is subclassed as H Group or an olivine-bronzite chondrite.
    Meteorites are bits of rock that are captured by a planet's
    gravity and pulled to the surface. This meteorite is of a type named
    chondrite and is thought to have formed at the same time as the planets
    in the solar nebula, about 4.55 billion years ago.
    <i>(Copyright Calvin J. Hamilton)</i>
