    <b>Chondrite Meteorite Slice</b>
    <br>
    This is a section from a stone chondrite meteorite that fell in 1852 in Harghita, Romania.
    <i>(Copyright Calvin J. Hamilton)</i>
    <br clear="all"><br>
        <img src="../images/solar/meteoroids.jpg" alt="Chondrite Meteorite" border="1" width="200" height="151" class="left">
    <b>Chondrite Meteorite Showing Regmaglypts</b>
    <br>
    This meteorite fell in 1924. Notice the depreessions on this sample.
    These are called <b>regmaglypts</b> and are most likely paralled to the air
